pair.value: This process will be responsible for updating user profiles and group membership using information from LDAP and the AMP database.
Deactivate Users found in the AMP Application Users group but not in the LDAP group
Determine if there are users that need to be deactivated
Send Alert of LDAP Synch Completion
Alert that LDAP Synch Completed Successfully

acp.name: Message
acp.a:expr:
=concatenate("

The LDAP Synch successfully completed.

 

",length(pv!totalUserList_texts)," Users were found in LDAP.

",length(pv!usersCreated_texts)," Users were created.

",length(pv!usersToDeactivate_texts)," Users were deactivated.

",length(pv!ldapUsersFailed_texts)," Users failed to get updated by the synch.

")

pair.value: Send Alert of LDAP Failure to Complete
Alert that LDAP Synch Completed Successfully

acp.name: Message
acp.a:expr:
=concatenate("

The LDAP Synch process has been running for ",#"_a-0000d62a-9e0e-8000-ac7a-680000680000_7565"," hours and has not yet completed.

 

Please investigate the process by clicking ",linktoprocessdashboard(pp!id, "here"),".

")

pair.value: Compare the listing of LDAP users to the listing of Application users to see who needs to be deactivated

This node is used for completing some additional calculations for report purposes.
Currently, this node is only used for calculating the new users added
Compare the listing of LDAP users to the listing of Application users to see who needs to be deactivated.

annotation.text: Perform a group by group synch between Appian and LDAP groups. Then use a listing of all App Users as dictated by LDAP, to determine what Appian users should be deactivated.
